Enable Search Insights (Ask Data for Salesforce)

Bring intelligent, self-service analytics to the CRM Analytics Home page with Ask Data for Salesforce and Search Insights.

REQUIRED EDITIONS
Available in CRM Analytics in Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience.
CRM Analytics is available for an extra cost in Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited Editions. Also available in Developer Edition
Available with the CRM Analytics Plus license.

Ask Data for Salesforce is enabled by default in production orgs with 1,000 or more reports, plus active use of the Analytics Home page. It's also available for Full sandboxes upon request.

If Ask Data for Salesforce was disabled at some point and now you want to enable it, complete the following steps.

From Setup, enter Analytics in the Quick Find box, then select Settings.
Select Enable Search Insights.
Click Save.
Ask Data for Salesforce becomes available 24 hours after it’s enabled.
title: Enable Search Insights in CRM Analytics
